OL,5, A black Uber Eats driver has received a
OL,6, payout after "racially discriminatory" 
OL,7, facial-recognition checks prevented him
OL,8, accessing the app to secure work.      
OL,10,FWhen Pa Edrissa Manjang began working  
OL,11,Ffor Uber Eats, in November 2019, its   
OL,12,Fapp did not regularly ask him to send  
OL,13,Fselfies in order to register for jobs. 
OL,15,FBut the Microsoft-powered Uber Eats app
OL,16,Fincreased these verification checks.   
OL,18,FAnd in 2021, it said after "careful    
OL,19,Fconsideration" his account would be    
OL,20,Fremoved, due to "continued mismatches".
